<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6360&amp;p=27749#p27749"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">highstream wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Just tried to install Aero Glass and got the error in the lower screenshot. What should I make of it? Then there's the Aero Glass for Win8.1 etc. on the desktop right on top of the trash icon (moved the latter a little). What's with that? Thanks,<br /><br />Yes, I think you're right about the page sizing, although I would think the forum coding would scale it. But then there's the text size, which is magnified in some browsers and not in others.<br /></div><br /><br />Ignore the incompatability message. That happens in Windows 10. It still works, just ignore the message. It will pop up every time you login but it's not an issue. AeroGlass still works. As for the text in the bottom right corner, that's just a watermark. It can be removed by donating $5 USD to BigMuscle via the website but that's practically all that gets effected.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4140">Nimbi</a> — Fri Jul 22, 2016 2:54 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
